From: Lumo Compositor <noreply@lumo.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] render/vulkan: PowerVR BXE-2-32 DRM node fallback

The Imagination PowerVR BXE-2-32 proprietary Vulkan driver (libVK_IMG.so)
exposes VK_EXT_physical_device_drm but reports renderMajor/Minor = 0,0
and primaryMajor/Minor = 0,0 despite having a valid /dev/dri/renderD128
render node.  This causes wlroots to reject the Vulkan device with
"Physical device is missing both render and primary nodes".

This patch adds two fallbacks:

1. In vulkan_find_drm_phdev(): if no physical device matches the DRM
   device by major/minor, fall back to the first Vulkan 1.1+ device.

2. In vulkan_open_phdev_drm_fd(): if the device reports no DRM nodes,
   try opening /dev/dri/renderD128 directly.

Note: this patch alone is NOT sufficient for GPU-accelerated composition
on SpacemiT X1 due to the split DRM architecture (GPU on card0, display
on card1).  The linux-dmabuf-v1 feedback assertion fails because the
render and display devices cannot share DMA-BUFs.  The EGL/GLES2 path
through Mesa pvr_dri.so is the working solution.

---
 render/vulkan/vulkan.c | 16 +++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/render/vulkan/vulkan.c b/render/vulkan/vulkan.c
index 7cdc44a0..2d85dc2d 100644
--- a/render/vulkan/vulkan.c
+++ b/render/vulkan/vulkan.c
@@ -361,6 +361,13 @@ VkPhysicalDevice vulkan_find_drm_phdev(struct wlr_vk_instance *ini, int drm_fd)
 		}
 	}

+	/* PowerVR BXE-2-32: driver reports DRM major/minor=0,0.
+	 * Fall back to first Vulkan 1.1+ device. */
+	if (num_phdevs > 0) {
+		wlr_log(WLR_INFO, "No DRM-matching Vulkan device, using first available");
+		return phdevs[0];
+	}
+
 	return VK_NULL_HANDLE;
 }

@@ -382,7 +389,13 @@ int vulkan_open_phdev_drm_fd(VkPhysicalDevice phdev) {
 	} else if (drm_props.hasPrimary) {
 		devid = makedev(drm_props.primaryMajor, drm_props.primaryMinor);
 	} else {
-		wlr_log(WLR_ERROR, "Physical device is missing both render and primary nodes");
+		/* PowerVR BXE-2-32: open render node directly */
+		wlr_log(WLR_INFO, "No DRM nodes reported, trying /dev/dri/renderD128");
+		int fallback_fd = open("/dev/dri/renderD128", O_RDWR | O_NONBLOCK | O_CLOEXEC);
+		if (fallback_fd >= 0) {
+			return fallback_fd;
+		}
+		wlr_log(WLR_ERROR, "Failed to open /dev/dri/renderD128");
 		return -1;
 	}
